{"doc":{"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"transition","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"en-US","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS\">CSS</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Reference\">CSS Reference</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Transitions\">CSS Transitions</a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Guides</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Transitions/Using_CSS_transitions\">Using CSS transitions</a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-delay\"><code>transition-delay</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-duration\"><code>transition-duration</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-property\"><code>transition-property</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-timing-function\"><code>transition-timing-function</code></a></li><li><em><code>transition</code></em></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div></div>\n\n<p>The <strong><code>transition</code></strong> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS\">CSS </a>property is a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Shorthand_properties\">shorthand property</a> for <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-property\"><code>transition-property</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-duration\"><code>transition-duration</code></a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-timing-function\"><code>transition-timing-function</code></a>, and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-delay\"><code>transition-delay</code></a>.</p>\n\n<div><iframe class=\"interactive\" width=\"100%\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://interactive-examples.mdn.mozilla.net/pages/css/transition.html\" title=\"MDN Web Docs Interactive Example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>\n\n<p class=\"hidden\">The source for this interactive example is stored in a GitHub repository. If you'd like to contribute to the interactive examples project, please clone <a href=\"https://github.com/mdn/interactive-examples\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">https://github.com/mdn/interactive-examples</a> and send us a pull request.</p></div>\n\n<p>Transitions enable you to define the transition between two states of an element. Different states may be defined using <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Pseudo-classes\">pseudo-classes</a> like <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:hover\"><code>:hover</code></a> or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/:active\"><code>:active</code></a> or dynamically set using JavaScript.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Constituent_properties","title":"Constituent properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p>This property is a shorthand for the following CSS properties:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-delay\"><code>transition-delay</code></a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-duration\"><code>transition-duration</code></a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-property\"><code>transition-property</code></a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-timing-function\"><code>transition-timing-function</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"brush:css no-line-numbers notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">/* Apply to 1 property */</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* property name | duration */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> margin-right 4s<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* property name | duration | delay */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> margin-right 4s 1s<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* property name | duration | easing function */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> margin-right 4s ease-in-out<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* property name | duration | easing function | delay */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> margin-right 4s ease-in-out 1s<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* Apply to 2 properties */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> margin-right 4s<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> color 1s<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* Apply to all changed properties */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> all 0.5s ease-out<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">/* Global values */</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> inherit<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> initial<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> unset<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>The <code>transition</code> property is specified as one or more single-property transitions, separated by commas.</p>\n\n<p>Each single-property transition describes the transition that should be applied to a single property (or the special values <code>all</code> and <code>none</code>). It includes:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>zero or one value representing the property to which the transition should apply. This may be any one of:\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li>the keyword <code>none</code></li>\n\t\t<li>the keyword <code>all</code></li>\n\t\t<li>a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/custom-ident\"><code>&lt;custom-ident&gt;</code></a> naming a CSS property.</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>zero or one <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/easing-function\"><code>&lt;easing-function&gt;</code></a> value representing the easing function to use</li>\n\t<li>zero, one, or two <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/time\"><code>&lt;time&gt;</code></a> values. The first value that can be parsed as a time is assigned to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-duration\"><code>transition-duration</code></a>, and the second value that can be parsed as a time is assigned to <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-delay\"><code>transition-delay</code></a>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>See <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Transitions/Using_CSS_transitions#when_property_value_lists_are_of_different_lengths\">how things are handled</a> when lists of property values aren't the same length. In short, extra transition descriptions beyond the number of properties actually being animated are ignored.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Formal_definition","title":"Formal definition","isH3":false,"content":"<p><table class=\"properties\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/initial_value\">Initial value</a></th><td>as each of the properties of the shorthand:<br><ul><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-delay\"><code>transition-delay</code></a>: <code>0s</code></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-duration\"><code>transition-duration</code></a>: <code>0s</code></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-property\"><code>transition-property</code></a>: all</li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-timing-function\"><code>transition-timing-function</code></a>: <code>ease</code></li></ul></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Applies to</th><td>all elements, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::before\"><code>::before</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::after\"><code>::after</code></a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Pseudo-elements\">pseudo-elements</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/inheritance\">Inherited</a></th><td>no</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/computed_value\">Computed value</a></th><td>as each of the properties of the shorthand:<br><ul><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-delay\"><code>transition-delay</code></a>: as specified</li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-duration\"><code>transition-duration</code></a>: as specified</li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-property\"><code>transition-property</code></a>: as specified</li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition-timing-function\"><code>transition-timing-function</code></a>: as specified</li></ul></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Animation type</th><td>discrete</td></tr></tbody></table></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Formal_syntax","title":"Formal syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<pre class=\"notranslate\"><a href=\"#single-transition\">&lt;single-transition&gt;</a><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#hash_mark_()\" title=\"Hash mark: the entity is repeated one or several times, each occurence separated by a comma\">#</a><p style=\"font-family:Open Sans,Arial,sans-serif; margin: 10px 0 0 0;\">where <br><code style=\"font-family:Consolas,Monaco,&quot;Andale Mono&quot;,monospace;\"><span id=\"single-transition\">&lt;single-transition&gt;</span> = <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#brackets\" title=\"Brackets: enclose several entities, combinators, and multipliers to transform them as a single component\">[</a> none <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> <a href=\"#single-transition-property\">&lt;single-transition-property&gt;</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#brackets\" title=\"Brackets: enclose several entities, combinators, and multipliers to transform them as a single component\">]</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#double_bar\" title=\"Double bar: one or several of the entities must be present, in any order\">||</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/time\" title=\"Possible values: a number followed by's' or 'ms', like 3s, -2.5ms or 0s.\">&lt;time&gt;</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#double_bar\" title=\"Double bar: one or several of the entities must be present, in any order\">||</a> <a href=\"#easing-function\">&lt;easing-function&gt;</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#double_bar\" title=\"Double bar: one or several of the entities must be present, in any order\">||</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/time\" title=\"Possible values: a number followed by's' or 'ms', like 3s, -2.5ms or 0s.\">&lt;time&gt;</a></code></p><p style=\"font-family:Open Sans,Arial,sans-serif; margin: 10px 0 0 0;\">where <br><code style=\"font-family:Consolas,Monaco,&quot;Andale Mono&quot;,monospace;\"><span id=\"single-transition-property\">&lt;single-transition-property&gt;</span> = all <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/custom-ident\" title=\"\">&lt;custom-ident&gt;</a><br><span id=\"easing-function\">&lt;easing-function&gt;</span> = linear <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> <a href=\"#cubic-bezier-timing-function\">&lt;cubic-bezier-timing-function&gt;</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> <a href=\"#step-timing-function\">&lt;step-timing-function&gt;</a></code></p><p style=\"font-family:Open Sans,Arial,sans-serif; margin: 10px 0 0 0;\">where <br><code style=\"font-family:Consolas,Monaco,&quot;Andale Mono&quot;,monospace;\"><span id=\"cubic-bezier-timing-function\">&lt;cubic-bezier-timing-function&gt;</span> = ease <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> ease-in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> ease-out <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> ease-in-out <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> cubic-bezier(<number <a=\"\" href=\"/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Brackets\" title=\"Brackets: enclose several entities, combinators, and multipliers to transform them as a single component\">[0,1<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#brackets\" title=\"Brackets: enclose several entities, combinators, and multipliers to transform them as a single component\">]</a>&gt;, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/number\" title=\"\">&lt;number&gt;</a>, <number <a=\"\" href=\"/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Brackets\" title=\"Brackets: enclose several entities, combinators, and multipliers to transform them as a single component\">[0,1<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#brackets\" title=\"Brackets: enclose several entities, combinators, and multipliers to transform them as a single component\">]</a>&gt;, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/number\" title=\"\">&lt;number&gt;</a>)<br><span id=\"step-timing-function\">&lt;step-timing-function&gt;</span> = step-start <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> step-end <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> steps(<a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/integer\" title=\"\">&lt;integer&gt;</a><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#brackets\" title=\"Brackets: enclose several entities, combinators, and multipliers to transform them as a single component\">[</a>, <a href=\"#step-position\">&lt;step-position&gt;</a><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#brackets\" title=\"Brackets: enclose several entities, combinators, and multipliers to transform them as a single component\">]</a><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#question_mark_()\" title=\"Question mark: the entity is optional\">?</a>)</number></number></code></p><p style=\"font-family:Open Sans,Arial,sans-serif; margin: 10px 0 0 0;\">where <br><code style=\"font-family:Consolas,Monaco,&quot;Andale Mono&quot;,monospace;\"><span id=\"step-position\">&lt;step-position&gt;</span> = jump-start <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> jump-end <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> jump-none <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> jump-both <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> start <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#single_bar\" title=\"Single bar: exactly one of the entities must be present\">|</a> end</code></p></pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Simple_example","title":"Simple example","isH3":true,"content":"<p>This example performs a four-second font size transition with a one-second delay when the user hovers over the element.</p>\n\n<h4 id=\"HTML\">HTML</h4>\n\n<pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>a</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>target<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>Hover over me<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>a</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span></code></pre>\n\n<h4 id=\"CSS\">CSS</h4>\n\n<pre class=\"brush: css notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token selector\">.target</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 14px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">transition</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> font-size 4s 1s<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token selector\">.target:hover</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 36px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><iframe class=\"sample-code-frame\" id=\"frame_Simple_example\" width=\"600\" height=\"100\" src=\"https://yari-demos.prod.mdn.mozit.cloud/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition/_samples_/Simple_example\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></p>\n\n<p>There are several more examples of CSS transitions included in the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Transitions/Using_CSS_transitions\">Using CSS transitions</a> article.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"Specifications","title":"Specifications","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n\t<thead>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<th scope=\"col\">Specification</th>\n\t\t\t<th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n\t\t\t<th scope=\"col\">Comment</th>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</thead>\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td><a href=\"https://drafts.csswg.org/css-transitions/#transition-shorthand-property\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">CSS Transitions<br><small lang=\"en-US\">The definition of 'transition' in that specification.</small></a></td>\n\t\t\t<td><span class=\"spec-wd\">Working Draft</span></td>\n\t\t\t<td>Initial definition</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"Browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"css.properties.transition","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"See_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n\t<li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Transitions/Using_CSS_transitions\">Using CSS transitions</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TransitionEvent\"><code>TransitionEvent</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Constituent properties","id":"Constituent_properties"},{"text":"Syntax","id":"Syntax"},{"text":"Formal definition","id":"Formal_definition"},{"text":"Formal syntax","id":"Formal_syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"Examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"Specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"Browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"See_also"}],"summary":"The transition CSS property is a shorthand property for transition-property, transition-duration, transition-timing-function, and transition-delay.","popularity":0.0822,"modified":"2021-03-15T17:55:56.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"transition","url":"/bg/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"bg"},{"title":"transition","url":"/de/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"de"},{"title":"transition","url":"/es/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"es"},{"title":"transition","url":"/fr/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"fr"},{"title":"transition","url":"/ja/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"ja"},{"title":"transition","url":"/ko/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"ko"},{"title":"transition","url":"/pt-BR/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"pt-BR"},{"title":"transition","url":"/ru/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"ru"},{"title":"transition","url":"/zh-CN/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"zh-CN"},{"title":"transition","url":"/zh-TW/docs/Web/CSS/transition","locale":"zh-TW"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/css/transition","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/css/transition/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/f4fb4c2d90a134366c280eec6cb599825981ad5d"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS","title":"CSS: Cascading Style Sheets"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transition","title":"transition"}],"pageTitle":"transition - CSS: Cascading Style Sheets | MDN","noIndexing":false}}